them I am sick. How do you propose to justify that disregard for our
daughters?

Ms. Boyce, it was your client that was said she was concerned with
consistency, yet numerous documents show demonstrates no concern for
consistency, and a refusal for a schedule during the summer. At times she
demands supervision, location, supervisor and time limits based not on the
girl=E2=80=99s best interests but those of her elderly parents. She refused=
 to
allow my mother to supervise and has shown no concern for the relationship
that she has developed with the girls. And then she asks her, without
consulting me, to take responsibility for driving. Be it notes one of her
allegations is that I will take and withhold the girls from her. Ms. Holmes
behavior reveals a pattern that is directed toward minimizing the girls
right to develop an independent relationship with me, to their confusion
and detriment.

