client=E2=80=99s concern was merely to be notified if I was unavailable (mi=
nutes of
meeting with CAS). She has consistently exerted a more invasive approach
than CAS, with no evidence. She demanded and forcefully walked into my
living space, including bedroom, after being asked not to. The onus is on
her to prove her allegations, which CAS has confirmed they will not be
investigating.

She has taken the girls away from me without explanation to me or the girls
on three unfounded occasions. When I was struggling with addiction it was
justified. In contrast, at the end of the summer she raised no safety
concerns but merely informed me of the access schedule, based on how busy
the girls were. Only later did I find out from the girls that four nights
of activities turned into one evening and an afternoon. The contradictions
continue and change, but consistently ensure that contact with me is
limited as much as possible, and now completely cut off. Her justifications
did not raise safety concerns and she did not take the necessary step of
notifying the appropriate authorities. She claims to have made the decision
with your support. She provided multiple and conflicting justifications but
seems to have settled most recently on medication. I have followed my
treatment plan, have full support of doctors and counsellors trained to
recognize such claims, and yet she dismisses them. Her actions suggest she
has expertise that supersedes my family doctor, sleep doctor/psychiatrist,
counselor, and Dr. Willows, head of addictions at the Royal Ottawa.

There is ample evidence of restricting the girls time with me, imposing her
own supervision and access schedule which is in breech of the court orders,
refuses to talk to me, mediate, work with a counsellor, or any other
alternative to the courts I have suggested. Furthermore, she is potentially
causing the girls anxiety by not being able to see me healthy and fit
during the pandemic, and confusing them by allowing her son Sam to move
between her home and his fathers, while restricting them from doing so. She
has also had visitors and I have no idea if she is following Covid-19
guidelines. I certainly see the girls wrestling and playing.

