simply time to end the conversation, or she will only allow the girls to
call immediately before snacks and a movie, which diverts their attention.

-          Why is she ignoring the fact that CAS sees no grounds for
concern, and the fact that they are not opening an investigation?

-          Please explain to me why, contrary to legal precedent, she
presumes her decisions supersede those of the court, CAS, and me.

-          Which of the reasons provided for refusing to follow our
settlement is she going to argue, will it change, and what evidence, aside
from hearsay, can she provide?

-          Why is Ben no longer living with either parent, and does it have
to do with the girls?

-          Can you please respond to my question if you represent Ms.
Holmes, or if there has been a change?

-          Finally, on what grounds has your client refused to exercise
joint custody?

These questions are asked after the Chief Justice has stated that even in
the face of a pandemic parties must comply with orders.

