record. Her actions interfere with my daughters right to have a
relationship with me.

Your client continues to illegally withhold Charlotte and Alice from access
from me based on her own assessment and hearsay from parties that have not
had any significant contact with me. And yet during much of the time she
did allow some unsupervised access. Her behavior works against her duty to
the principle of maximum contact, which is in the girl=E2=80=99s best inter=
est, and
suggests her concerns are not genuine, following what a parent is expected
to do,

Furthermore, your client has admitted to physically abusing her oldest son,
and I have witnessed her verbally abuse him.

This is an extremely unfortunate situation, but it has allowed me not only
time to research case law but to access legal aid and other resources. Your
client is putting herself in a position that courts have consistently ruled
against, and in some cases reversing access Have you informed her of all of
the possible outcomes that could arise, and what I may be requesting when
the courts return to normal?

For know, unless your client agrees to the settlement signed in your
office, I have done all I can to avoid court, while you and Ms. Holmes have
done all you can to ignore me. Setting up a situation such as she has is
not grounds for a claim for status quo. It is contrived, and case law
