It is worth reading the conclusion from the Chief Justice: =E2=80=9CThis su=
spension
will cause substantial inconvenience to those with matters before the
Court. The decision to engage this emergency process was not made lightly.
However, the health and safety of the public, as well as all justice
participants is a priority.

We ask for and appreciate your co-operation, flexibility and understanding
during this extraordinary time.=E2=80=9D

These are two girls with incredible potential that deserve to have their
interests made central. And so says the law.

I have seen no evidence of any attempt to cooperate. Yet I have tried to
engage both of you constructively, I have suggested solutions rather than
threats, bringing this to court leaves life long decisions up to a judge
who is already overburdened; it is in the interest of the girls for us to
try to negotiate, and unburden the court.

Let us ask ourselves how we should be conducting ourselves, and reflect on
how, most important your client is affecting the girls.

Your client allows some communication, but also blocks it and is usually
present, in Face Time, or talking for or over the girls. She has shown no
concern for the girls=E2=80=99 relationship with my mother, yet claims dist=
ant
relatives take precedence over me.

I make no claims to know her thoughts or intentions, but she has provided
ample evidence in her conduct, decisions, and assumption of sovereignty
over all decisions.

So, an urgent motion for access which can be arranged and follow provincial
health guidelines. And because your client knew and waited until I gave
notice and committed to this, more expensive place as per our agreement to
cease child support so we can return to shared custody, I am in financial
hardship and do not have a place to live as of the 1st of May. The courts
have been hearing dire issues regarding financial circumstances and have
begun to expand what they will hear as of 6 April 2020.

Finally, I find it sad and unfortunate that she has taken these steps. I
sincerely hope she maintains a close and healthy relationship with our
daughters through their lives, but while I will not share the details of
her allegations and actions, families talk, and the girls may come to
resent her, which would be unfortunate. I have always maintained that I
will support their relationship with their mother, without interfering or
trying to affect it. It is their right to have a relationship with each of
us without interference.

This is an evolving situation, but I would direct your attention to Ribeiro
V. Wright as an example: even the unprecedented Covid-19 pandemic does not
equal cancellation of parenting time. Yet your client has not raised
Covid-19, instead relying on aggression, entering my place of residence
after explicitly being asked not to, and making false claims that I was out
of communications. Those communications are the basis of her confrontation
and aggression. They will be evidence, as opposed to allegations.

I will be filling, but as I have said before if your client cooperates, and
she has proven she can and will, we can avoid court and focus our concern
on the well-being of the girls. They deserve it, I is law, and the only
basis a judge can rule on.

I hope, but do not expect to hear from you. But your client can do better
and is obliged to do so for the girls.

 Darryl

